record_data.record_plain_text: CED White River Solar, LLC Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Co-Tenancy and Common Facilities Agreement ETariff Information Tariff Submitter: CED White River Solar, LLC FERC Tariff Program Name: FERC FPA Electric MBR Tariff Title: Rate Schedules and Tariffs Tariff Record Proposed Effective Date: April 28, 2014 Tariff Record Title: FERC Rate Schedule No. 1, CED White River Solar, LLC Option Code: A EXECUTION VERSION 4812-9092-4561.2OHSUSA:751106638.3 CO-TENANCY AND COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT [WHITE RIVER PROJECTS] THIS CO-TENANCY AND COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this Agreement ), dated as of October 30, 2012, is made and entered into by and between SPS WHITE RIVER, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ( SPS White River ), and SPS WHITE RIVER WEST, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ( SPS West , and together with SPS White River, the Parties, and each, a Party ). All capitalized terms not otherwise defined in this Agreement shall have the meaning set forth in Article 1. RECITALS A. SPS White River plans to develop, construct, own and operate a 20 MW solar power generation Project to be located on the SPS White River Project Site. SPS White River leases the SPS White River Project Site from the Lessors pursuant to the SPS White River Project Lease. B. SPS West plans to develop, construct, own and operate a 19.75 MW solar power generation Project to be located on the SPS West Project Site. SPS West intends to lease the SPS West Project Site from the Lessors pursuant to the SPS West Project Lease. C. The SPS White River Project and the SPS West Project intend to utilize certain Common Facilities located on the Shared Premises in connection with their respective Projects. D. SPS White River and SPS West are each a party to a Non-Exclusive Easement, pursuant to which SPS White River and SPS West are each independently granted rights to the Shared Premises from the Lessors. E. It is anticipated that SPS White River will commence construction of the SPS White River Project prior to the commencement of construction by SPS West of the SPS West Project, and that SPS White River will construct the Common Facilities. F. Subject to certain conditions precedent as more particularly described herein, SPS White River has agreed to assign, transfer, and convey to SPS West, effective as of the later of the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project and the Effective Date of this Agreement, an Undivided Interest. G. The Common Facilities will be operated and managed by the Operator pursuant to the O&M Agreement, and the Parties intend to have the Operator be responsible for operation, maintenance and repair of the Common Facilities and to share the costs of the Operator as provided herein. H. The Parties intend to seek mutual economic benefits by jointly bearing the cost of certain Shared Expenses. 2 4812-9092-4561.2 I. The Parties are entering into this Agreement to govern their respective rights and obligations with respect to the Shared Premises, the Shared Expenses and their Undivided Interests, which will be the Parties expression of their intention to establish and impose mutually beneficial limitations, restrictions, covenants and conditions to provide for the proper and orderly ownership, operation and management of their interests in the respective Projects. AGREEMENT NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, each of the Parties hereby agrees as follows: ARTICLE ONE DEFINITIONS The following capitalized terms will have the respective meanings set forth below: Affiliate means, with respect to a Person, any other Person that, directly or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, Controls, is Controlled by or is under common Control with such first Person. Agreement means this Co-Tenancy and Common Facilities Agreement, as amended from time to time. Bankruptcy Event means, with respect to any Party, such Party: (i) voluntarily files a petition or otherwise commences, authorizes or acquiesces in the commencement of a proceeding or cause of action under any bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or similar law, or has any such petition filed or commenced against it by its creditors and such petition is not dismissed within sixty (60) days of the filing or commencement or an order for relief is entered; (ii) makes an assignment or any general arrangement for the benefit of creditors; (iii) otherwise becomes insolvent, however evidenced; (iv) has a liquidator, administrator, receiver, trustee, conservator or similar official appointed with respect to it or any substantial portion of its property or assets; or (v) is generally unable to pay its debts as they fall due. Common Facilities means the assets and facilities located on the Shared Premises and described in Exhibit A-1, and any future facilities on the Shared Premises which the Parties contemplate will be subject to common ownership and use in accordance with this Agreement. Construction Start Date means, for any Project, the date of such Project s commencement of construction. Control means the possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of the management or policies of a Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities, in its capacity as a sole or managing member, by Contract, or otherwise. The term Control when used as a verb in the referenced clauses shall have a correlative meaning. Default Rate means an interest rate of one percent (1%) per month. 3 4812-9092-4561.2 Demand has the meaning specified in Section 10.3(d). Demanding Party has the meaning specified in Section 10.3(d). Effective Date means the date when Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ( FERC ) has accepted this Agreement and allowed it to become effective and granted waiver of FERC s open access transmission requirements. "Emergency" shall mean any occurrence, in the reasonable judgment of a Party that may arise that requires immediate action and which constitutes a serious actual or potential hazard to the safety of persons or property, or may materially interfere with the safe, economical or environmentally sound operation of the Common Facilities or the Shared Premises. Event of Default has the meaning specified in Section 9.1. Force Majeure shall mean any act, casualty or occurrence, condition, event or circumstance of any kind or nature not reasonably within the excused party s control and which could not have been avoided by reasonable measures, including: (i) acts of God or the elements (including fire, earthquake, explosion, flood, epidemic or any other casualty or accident) or condemnation; (ii) strikes, lock outs or other labor disputes; (iii) the inability to secure labor or materials in the open market; and (iv) war, terrorism, sabotage, civil strife or other violence. Force Majeure expressly does not include late delivery or breakage of equipment or materials or economic hardship except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event. IE Report means a report of the Independent Engineer confirming that the Common Facilities have been constructed in reasonable conformance with the Final Design Documents. Impairment means a measurable increase in operating costs, a measurable reduction in performance or capacity of a Project or the Common Facilities, or a demonstrated increase in operating risks of a Project or the Common Facilities. Independent Engineer means the independent engineer to be engaged to prepare the IE Report, which shall be an entity selected by SPS White River subject to the approval of SPS West, such approval not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed. Initial Owners means SPS White River and SPS West. Laws means all applicable laws, statutes, ordinances, rules, regulations, decrees, policies, orders, permits, requirements, judgments, decisions, injunctions and findings of or issued by any governmental authority, including laws relating to health, safety and the environment. Lessors means Steve W. Martin and Joann Martin, Trustees of the Martin Family Trust dated April 2, 2011, and Steve W. Martin Ranch, Inc., a California corporation. Non-Exclusive Easement and Non-Exclusive Easements means, as applicable, (a) the Access and Use Easement Agreement (White River) between the Lessors and SPS White River dated as of September 19, 2012, a memorandum of which was recorded in the Official Records 4 4812-9092-4561.2 of Tulare County, California on October __, 2012 as Instrument No. 2012- __________________, and/or (b) the Access and Use Easement Agreement (White River West) contemplated to be entered into in the future between the Lessors and SPS West, in the form prescribed by the SPS West Project Lease. Non-Pledging Party has the meaning specified in Section 8.2(b). O&M Agreement means the Operations and Maintenance Contract to be entered into between SPS White River and the Operator, which agreement shall relate to, among other matters, the operation, maintenance and repair of the Common Facilities, and which agreement shall be negotiated by SPS White River and subject to the approval of SPS West, such approval not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed. Operator means the Operator under the O&M Agreement, which shall be an entity selected by SPS White River subject to the approval of SPS West, such approval not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed. Party or Parties has the meaning specified in the preamble to the Agreement. Person means any individual, sole proprietorship, corporation, partnership, joint venture, limited liability partnership, limited liability company, trust, unincorporated association, institution or any other entity. Pledging Party has the meaning specified in Section 8.2(b). Project means the solar power generation facilities and related equipment owned or to be owned by each Party. Project Controlled Assets means, for each Party, such Party s Project and the corresponding Project Site. Project Percentage Interest means the percentage interest of each Party in the Common Facilities and in the Shared Expenses, which percentage interests shall be 50.00% in the case of SPS White River and 50.00% in the case of SPS West. Project Sites means, together, the SPS White River Site and the SPS West Site. Reimbursable Costs shall mean all reasonable and documented costs incurred by SPS White River associated with the Common Facilities, including, but not limited to, costs incurred in connection with the design, construction, maintenance, operation, and repair of the Common Facilities, insurance premiums for builder s all-risk or other casualty insurance obtained by SPS White River during the construction of the Common Facilities, and payments made by SPS White River to the Lessors pursuant to Section 16.2 of the SPS White River Project Lease, determined in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. The Parties currently estimate that the Reimbursable Costs associated with the design and construction of the Common Facilities will be approximately one hundred forty thousand dollars ($140,000). Reimbursable Costs Schedule has the meaning specified in Section 3.1(d). 5 4812-9092-4561.2 Reimbursable O&M Costs has the meaning specified in Section 7.2(a). Rules has the meaning specified in Section 10.3. Secured Party shall mean (i) the agent or lead bank or lending institution under a loan agreement with a Party or other entity secured by any of the Shared Premises, Common Facilities, or all or a portion of Party s Undivided Interest, (ii) the "owner lessor" or other entity acquiring a Project or undivided ownership interest therein pursuant to a lease financing or (iii) any other party acknowledged by the Parties as a Secured Party in writing. Shared Expense Administrator shall mean SPS White River, or such replacement as is appointed pursuant to Section 9.3. Shared Expenses means certain common expenses necessary for the operation, maintenance and repair of the Common Facilities which are not within the scope of the O&M Agreement, but are intended by the Parties to be shared among the Projects, as more fully described on Exhibit A-2. Shared Premises means the Shared Facilities Joint Use Area as defined in and which is the subject of the Non-Exclusive Easements. The legal description, and a graphical depiction, of the Shared Premises is set forth on Exhibit A-3. SPS West means SPS White River West, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company. SPS West Project means the Project owned by SPS West. SPS West Project Lease means that certain Site Lease between SPS West and the Lessors, which SPS West intends to enter into under and pursuant to the terms of that certain Master Lease Agreement dated as of February 27, 2009, between the Lessors and SPS West (as successor-in-interest to ENCO Utility Services, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, and SPS White River), as amended by that certain Amendment to Master Lease, dated as of October 7, 2001, and that certain Amendment to and Assignment of Master Lease and Amendment to Memorandum of Lease among the Lessors, SPS White River and SPS West dated as of December 23, 2011, a memorandum of which Amendment to and Assignment of Master Lease and Amendment to Memorandum of Lease was recorded in the Official Records of Tulare County, California on December 27, 2011 as Instrument No. 2011-0079595, as further amended by that certain Third Amendment to Master Lease between SPS West and the Lessors, dated as of September 19, 2012, a memorandum of which was recorded in the Official Records of Tulare County, California on October ___, 2012 as Instrument No. [________]. Pursuant to such instrument, SPS West is the current Lessee under such Master Lease Agreement. SPS West Project Site means the lands underlying the SPS West Project which are expected to be the subject of the SPS West Project Lease, and which are described in Exhibit C- 1. SPS White River means SPS White River, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company. SPS White River Project means the Project owned by SPS White River. 6 4812-9092-4561.2 SPS White River Project Lease means that certain Site Lease between SPS White River and the Lessors, dated as of December 23, 2011, a memorandum of which was recorded in the Official Records of Tulare County, California on December 27, 2011 as Instrument No. 2011- 0079594, as amended by that certain First Amendment to Site Lease (White River) between SPS White River and the Lessors, dated as of September 19, 2012, a memorandum of which was recorded in the Official Records of Tulare County, California on October ___, 2012 as Instrument No. [_______]. SPS White River Project Site means the lands underlying the SPS White River Project which are the subject of the SPS White River Project Lease, which are described in Exhibit C-1. Surrendering Party has the meaning specified in Section 4.2. Transfer means to sell, transfer, assign, set over, deliver, convey, dispose of or otherwise demise an interest in tangible assets or intangible property, including this Agreement. Undivided Interest means an undivided interest, as a tenant in common, in and to the Common Facilities. ARTICLE TWO DECLARATION OF INTENTION; CONSTRUCTION OF COMMON FACILITIES 2.1 Declaration of Intention. The Parties hereby declare that their relationship in and to the Common Facilities is and will be that of tenants in common, expressly subject, however, to the terms, conditions, limitations and requirements set forth in this Agreement. Nothing contained in this Agreement will be deemed to constitute the Parties as partners or joint venturers. 2.2 Construction of Common Facilities. SPS White River shall be responsible for constructing the Common Facilities in accordance with the terms of this Agreement and shall be reimbursed for one-half of the Reimbursable Costs associated therewith as provided in Section 3.1(d). Prior to SPS White River commencing construction of the Common Facilities, SPS White River shall provide the proposed final design and specifications for the Common Facilities to SPS West (as revised as provided below (if applicable), the Final Design Documents ). SPS White River shall undertake its reasonable efforts to provide drafts of the Final Design Documents prior to their becoming proposed final designs and to consider any of SPS West s comments to such drafts. Within twenty (20) days of receiving the Final Design Documents, SPS West shall either (a) notify SPS White River that the Final Design Documents are acceptable to SPS West or (b) notify SPS White River that SPS West requests changes in the Final Design Documents based on the requirements of the SPS West Project, which notification shall include a written description in reasonable detail of the requested changes. If SPS West requests changes in the Final Design Documents, SPS White River shall accommodate such changes to the extent compatible with the requirements of the SPS White River Project and, if such changes are not compatible with the requirements of the SPS White River Project, the Parties shall negotiate expeditiously and in good faith to agree on changes to the Final Design Documents to accommodate the requirements of both Projects and the Final Design Documents shall include any such agreed changes; provided that if the Parties have not agreed on such changes within 7 4812-9092-4561.2 twenty (20) days after SPS White River s receipt of SPS West s request therefor, the Final Design Documents shall be considered to be acceptable with such changes as may have in good faith been proposed by SPS White River if (x) the Final Design Documents are in conformity with Pacific Gas & Electric Company s requirements and specifications for the Common Facilities and (y) Pacific Gas & Electric Company has approved the Final Design Documents as a design solution that will allow for the satisfactory interconnection of both the SPS West Project and the SPS White River Project, and in such event, SPS White River may proceed with the construction of the Common Facilities based on the Final Design Documents, but in no event prior to the Effective Date. ARTICLE THREE CONVEYANCE, COST REIMBURSEMENT, AND UNDIVIDED INTEREST IN COMMON FACILITIES AND SHARED PREMISES In exchange for payment of one dollar ($1.00) to each Party from each other Party and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged: 3.1 Transfer of Common Facilities by SPS White River. (a) SPS White River hereby Transfers to SPS West, effective as of the later of the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project or the Effective Date of this Agreement, an Undivided Interest in the amount of SPS West s Project Percentage Interest; provided, however, that if such Construction Start Date for the SPS West Project does not occur by January 1, 2019, then SPS White River shall retain all interest in the Common Facilities and this Agreement shall be of no further force or effect. (b) The Transfer will vest in SPS West its Project Percentage Interest in the Common Facilities, such that SPS White River and SPS West, effective as of the later of the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project or the Effective Date of this Agreement, together shall own one hundred percent (100%) of the Common Facilities. (c) A Party s use of any Common Facilities or the operation of its Project shall not in any way interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Party of its rights in such Common Facilities or the operation of its Project, any separate facilities or assets of such Party or the use and enjoyment by such other Party of its Project Controlled Assets, provided that a Party s use of the Common Facilities in compliance with this Agreement shall be deemed to not interfere with the other Party in violation of this Section 3.1(c). Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, each Party hereby consents to the development and operation of the Projects, and each of the Parties shall cooperate in good faith with the other Party s uses of the Common Facilities for the benefit of each others' Projects as contemplated by this Agreement. No Party will use or permit the use of the Common Facilities in any manner that would cause Impairment to the other Party s Project or the Common Facilities, or that would jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Common Facilities or any Laws as to the Common Facilities. (d) SPS West shall notify SPS White River in writing no later than thirty (30) 8 4812-9092-4561.2 days prior to the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project (the SPS West Commencement Notice ). Upon receipt of the SPS West Commencement Notice, SPS White River shall permit the Independent Engineer to inspect the Common Facilities, the Final Design Documents and any other design or construction documentation reasonably requested by the Independent Engineer, which inspection shall occur within ten (10) days following SPS West s receipt of the SPS West Commencement Notice. Within ten (10) days following receipt of the SPS West Commencement Notice, SPS White River shall provide SPS West with a schedule of (i) Reimbursable Costs previously incurred by SPS White River with respect to the Common Facilities and (ii) Reimbursable Costs reasonably estimated by SPS White River to be incurred with respect to the Common Facilities from the date of delivery of the schedule until the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project ( Reimbursable Costs Schedule ). If SPS West objects to the Reimbursable Costs Schedule, SPS West shall notify SPS White River within ten (10) days following SPS West s receipt of the Reimbursable Costs Schedule (which notice must specifically identify and state in reasonable detail the basis for the objection), and the Parties shall promptly convene a meeting to try and resolve the discrepancy. If the Parties are unable to resolve such discrepancy prior to the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project, the dispute shall be submitted to arbitration pursuant to the provisions of Section 10.3. (e) On the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project, but conditioned upon SPS West receiving the IE Report confirming that the Common Facilities have been constructed in reasonable conformance with the Final Design Documents, SPS West shall pay to SPS White River an amount equal to one-half (1/2) of all Reimbursable Costs set forth in the Reimbursable Costs Schedule. Such payment shall be made by wire transfer of immediately available federal funds in accordance with such instructions as may be provided by SPS White River. SPS West shall be solely responsible for, and shall pay to the appropriate governmental authorities, any federal, state, county and municipal transfer taxes payable in connection with the Transfer of the Common Facilities. Notwithstanding any objection or dispute relating to the Reimbursable Costs Schedule as provided in Section 3.1(d), pending the resolution of the objection or dispute pursuant to Section 10.3, SPS West shall pay to SPS White River the amount indicated as owing to SPS White River on the Reimbursable Costs Schedule and such objection or dispute shall not delay the construction or completion of the Common Facilities. If it is determined pursuant to the procedures of Section 10.3 that the Reimbursable Costs Schedule overstated the Reimbursable Costs owing to SPS White River pursuant to this Section 3.1(d), then an amount equal to the amount of such overstatement shall be promptly refunded to SPS West by SPS White River. 3.2 Shared Premises. The Non-Exclusive Easements allow for the construction, operation and maintenance of certain electrical facilities along and within the Shared Premises. To the extent permitted by applicable laws and regulations and subject to the terms and conditions of the Non-Exclusive Easements, each Party shall hold rights in the Shared Premises independently for the use of the Shared Premises, provided that each Party s right under its Non- Exclusive Easement is subject to the terms of this Agreement. 3.3 Shared Expenses; Interconnection. Each Party hereby confirms such Party s obligation to share in the periodic payment of Shared Expenses, and agrees, severally but not jointly, to pay such Party s Project Percentage Interest of the Shared Expenses as and when due and payable, provided that SPS West s initial payment with respect to Shared Expenses 9 4812-9092-4561.2 (including Shared Expenses incurred prior to the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project) shall be due and payable concurrently with the Reimbursable Costs being due and payable as provided in Section 3.1(e). The Parties will cause the Shared Expense Administrator, as authorized agent for each Party, to administer the collection and payment of the Shared Expenses, whether invoiced by each expense payee against a particular Project or invoiced as an aggregate expense of both Parties. Except as provided above with respect to SPS West s initial payment of the Shared Expenses, each Party will pay each invoice for Shared Expenses promptly upon, in any event within ten (10) days of, receipt of written notice thereof from the Shared Expense Administrator. As it becomes practicable and desirable, the Parties from time to time may designate additional expenses as Shared Expenses to be administered by the Shared Expense Administrator in accordance with this Section 3.3. Each further assumption of Shared Expense may be proposed by any Party, but will only be approved by an amendment to this Agreement. If any Party defaults in the payment of a Shared Expense, the other Party may make such payment, and the defaulting Party will promptly reimburse the paying Party and will owe interest on the amounts paid on such Party s behalf at the Default Rate. ARTICLE FOUR TERM 4.1 Term. The term of this Agreement will commence on the Effective Date, and, unless sooner terminated by mutual agreement of both Parties or the consolidation of ownership of the Common Facilities in a single Party, will continue as to each Party until the date of expiration or earlier termination of either Non-Exclusive Easement. 4.2 Surrender and Assignment of Undivided Interest. A Party who wishes to abandon and decommission its Project may elect to convey its Undivided Interest and assign its rights hereunder to the other Party and, thereupon, to cease to have any right, title or interest in the Common Facilities or its Undivided Interest (such Party a Surrendering Party ). The Surrendering Party must (a) deliver all instruments of transfer as may be necessary or appropriate to effect the conveyance of its Undivided Interest and assignment of its rights hereunder to, and which are reasonably satisfactory to, the remaining Party, (b) assign and convey to the remaining Party all its rights under this Agreement, provided, however, that (x) any such surrender of an encumbered Undivided Interest may only be surrendered with the written consent of each Secured Party that holds a security interest in such Undivided Interest and a release of such Secured Party s security interest being provided by such Secured Party, and (y) all necessary prior FERC approvals must be obtained and all Parties including the Surrendering Party must take all reasonable steps to obtain such FERC approval at the Surrendering Party s sole cost and expense, and (c) cure all Events of Default then existing on the part of the Surrendering Party. The Surrendering Party shall remain fully responsible for, and shall pay its Project Percentage Interest of, all Shared Expenses of such Surrendering Party and all Reimbursable Costs required to be paid by such Surrendering Party, if any, in each case that is due and payable through the effective date of its surrender of its Undivided Interest and all costs, including reasonable attorneys fees, incurred by the other Party in obtaining FERC approval of such surrender. No surrender of a Party s Undivided Interest shall relieve the Surrendering Party of any of its obligations (including but not limited to payment obligations due and payable through the effective date of its surrender of its Undivided Interest) under this Agreement, its Non-Exclusive Easement or any other agreement entered into pursuant to this Agreement, unless expressly 10 4812-9092-4561.2 provided for in this Agreement, or in a writing among the Parties. ARTICLE FIVE CONDITION OF PROPERTY AND COMPLIANCE WITH LAWS So long as SPS West receives an IE Report confirming that the Common Facilities have been constructed in reasonable conformance with the Final Design Documents as provided in Section 3.1(d), SPS West accepts the Common Facilities in their condition existing as of the date of Transfer to SPS West of a Project Percentage Interest therein, and subject to all Laws and all covenants, conditions, reservations, restrictions, easements, liens, encumbrances and other matters affecting the Common Facilities. SPS White River makes no warranty of any kind, express or implied with respect to the Common Facilities (except as to title to the Common Facilities by, through or under it). THE FOREGOING EXCLUSION OF ALL WARRANTIES BY SPS WHITE RIVER INCLUDES BUT IS NOT LIMITED TO IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF TITLE, SUITABILITY, MERCHANTABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. Each Party will, at such Party s own expense, conduct and cause the Operator to conduct all permitted activities and operations with respect to any Common Facilities (i) in a safe manner, (ii) in accordance with good operating practice, (iii) in compliance with all Laws, and (iv) without causing a material adverse effect on the other Party or the other Party s Project. ARTICLE SIX INDEMNITY, USE AND COMPLIANCE; INSURANCE 6.1 Indemnity. Each Party, for and on behalf of itself and its agents, successors and assigns, shall defend, indemnify and hold harmless the other Party and such other Party s directors, officers, partners, members, affiliates, employees, agents, successors and assigns, from and against any and all losses, liabilities, claims and damages suffered or incurred, to the extent they are both (i) (a) a result of the breach of this Agreement, failure to comply in any material respect with applicable Law, or the negligent acts or omissions, bad faith, gross negligence, or willful misconduct of the indemnifying Party or its directors, officers, partners, members, affiliates, employees, agents, successors and assigns, in connection with the indemnifying Party's Project, the Common Facilities or the performance of the indemnifying Party's duties and obligations under this Agreement, except to the extent caused by the indemnified Party's gross negligence or willful misconduct, or (b) are a result of outages or curtailment on the Common Facilities proximately caused by the indemnifying Party connecting its Project to the Common Facilities other than in accordance with the provisions hereof; and (ii) not otherwise covered by the insurance required by this Agreement. 6.2 Environmental Compliance. Without limiting the scope of each Party s obligations under Section 6.1, each Party will, with respect to such Party s Project Controlled Assets, be responsible for all investigations, studies, clean up, corrective actions or responses or remedial actions required by any governmental authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to such Party s use, operation or ownership of such Party s Project Controlled Assets. Each Party will have the right (but not the obligation, unless otherwise required above) to participate in the management and control of all investigations and any environmental clean up, remediation or related activities relating to such Party s Project 11 4812-9092-4561.2 Controlled Assets. 6.3 No Waste or Nuisance; Maintenance; No Interference. No Party will use or permit the use of the Common Facilities in any manner that would create waste or nuisance that would have a materially adverse effect on the Common Facilities, Project Sites or both, or that would increase the rate or jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Common Facilities, Project Sites or both. 6.4 Liens. Except as provided in Section 8.2, no Party will cause or permit any lien or encumbrance to be levied against or attached to the other Party s interests in the Common Facilities. 6.5 Regulatory Status. SPS White River represents and warrants that it is or has applied to be, and SPS West agrees that it will be prior to commencement of operation of the SPS West Project, qualified as an "exempt wholesale generator" ("EWG") as such term is defined in the Public Utility Holding Act of 2005, or a qualifying cogeneration or small power production facility, as defined in the Federal Power Act ("QF"), and the Parties each covenant to maintain their status as an EWG or a QF for so long as they are a party to this Agreement or have any interest in the Common Facilities. No Party will take any action that could adversely affect any other Party's ability to qualify as an EWG or a QF. 6.6 Outage or Disconnection. To the extent any Party's operating Project is disconnected from the Common Facilities or an outage of the Common Facilities occurs resulting in a loss of production and revenue to such Project, and the disconnection or outage is a result of another Party's breach of this Agreement, the breaching Party shall reimburse the Party that suffered the loss for such lost production and revenue within thirty (30) days of notice and supporting documentation of the loss, which supporting documentation shall include the applicable invoices from the applicable Party's power purchase agreement. 6.7 Insurance Requirements. Upon the later of the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project or the Effective Date of this Agreement, and thereafter for the duration of this Agreement the Parties shall, at their sole cost and expense, maintain the insurance policies and coverages described in Exhibit D-1. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Agreement, each Party waives any and every claim that arises or may arise against the other Party during the term of the Agreement for any and all loss of, or damage to any Common Facilities or such Party s Project, to the extent such loss or damage is an insured event covered by the insurance to be maintained in accordance with this Agreement and such insurance fully pays such claim. 6.8 Evidence, Terms and Modification of Insurance. Upon and after the later of the Construction Start Date of the SPS West Project or the Effective Date of this Agreement, except when the Parties are each a "named insured" under the same insurance policies required herein, each Party shall provide the other Party with insurance certificates reasonably acceptable to the other Party evidencing that insurance coverages are in compliance with this Agreement. In addition to the requirements set forth in Exhibit D-1, such insurance and certificates shall (i) provide a waiver of any and all rights of subrogation to the rights or claims of the other Party and the Lessors; and (ii) indicate that all policies have been endorsed as described above. All policies 12 4812-9092-4561.2 of a Party shall be written with insurers having an A.M. Best rating no less than "A- VII". All policies shall be written on an occurrence basis. All policies of a Party required by this Agreement shall be primary without right of contribution from any insurance which may be carried by the other Party or its employees, agents, representatives, members, directors and officers. No Party's liability under this Agreement is limited to the amount of insurance coverage required herein by virtue of this Section or insurance proceeds actually obtained. 6.9 Contractor's Insurance Requirements. For the duration of this Agreement, any contractor or subcontractor performing work on the Shared Premises shall, at its sole cost and expense, procure and maintain liability insurance policies and coverages in an amount required under the applicable service agreements or, if not specified therein, as reasonably required by the Parties and consistent with prudent industry practices. 6.10 Allocation of Insurance Proceeds. (a) Any proceeds of insurance received by a Party under the insurance policies required to be carried hereunder relating to a casualty event or event of loss with respect to a Party's Project may be applied by such Party in its sole discretion, provided that in the event a Party receives proceeds of insurance under such insurance policies relating to a casualty event or event of loss with respect to the Common Facilities, such insurance proceeds shall be held in trust by such Party until such loss proceeds are applied to the payment of the costs of repair or restoration of the Common Facilities relating to such casualty event or event of loss, in accordance with Section 6.10(b). (b) In the event that any portion of the Common Facilities are damaged or destroyed by a casualty event, the Parties shall arrange to rebuild the Common Facilities using such proceeds unless both Parties agree to the contrary; provided, however, that if the Parties cannot agree on the use of such proceeds within ten (10) days from the date of such damage or destruction, then either Party may elect to rebuild the Common Facilities at its own expense by delivery of written notice to the other Party; provided further, that any such rebuilding of the Common Facilities by a Party must be in reasonable conformance with the Final Design Documents. ARTICLE SEVEN OPERATION AND MANAGEMENT 7.1 Operator Performance Standard. Exhibit D-1-1 4812-9092-4561.2OHSUSA:751106638.3 EXHIBIT D-1 to CO-TENANCY AND COMMON FACILITIES AGREEMENT Insurance Requirements Property Insurance (a) Builder s All-Risk Insurance During Construction. During any construction of the Common Facilities each Party performing construction, shall procure or cause to be procured, and maintain or cause to be maintained, at its sole cost and expense, builder s risk insurance on an all-risk basis and on a replacement value form, in an amount (i) sufficient to replace any new or existing Common Facilities which are subject to such construction, and (ii) that is reasonably acceptable to the Party performing construction. (b) Operational Property Insurance. During operations each Party shall procure or cause to be procured, and maintain or cause to be maintained, at its sole cost and expense, all-risk property damage in an amount (i) sufficient to replace any existing Common Facilities that may be affected by a loss, and (ii) that is reasonably acceptable to the Parties. Other Insurance (a) General Liability Insurance. At all times each Party, shall procure or cause to be procured, and maintain liability insurance covering the respective activities of the Parties on the site of the Projects or the Shared Premises, including general liability coverage. Such coverage shall have a minimum combined occurrence and annual limitation of not less than One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) per occurrence and Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000) in the aggregate, and products/completed operations coverage a limitation of not less than Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000) for not less than three (3) years after completion of the Project. Such coverage shall also include umbrella liability coverage of not less than Ten Million Dollars ($10,000,000). Such coverage shall also contain contractual liability coverage and a separation of insureds clause. Furthermore, if a policy is on a claims made basis, such coverage shall survive the termination of this Agreement until the expiration of the maximum statutory period of limitations in the State of California for actions based on contract or in tort. If coverage is on an occurrence basis, insurance on an occurrence basis shall be maintained for the term of this Agreement. Each Party shall name the other Party and the Lessors as additional insureds and the insurance carried by either Party shall apply as primary and non-contributory insurance for claims arising from the Named Insured s sole negligence, and that the insurance carried by the Additional Insured will be excess only and will not contribute with the Primary Party s policy of insurance. (b) Workers Compensation. At all times, each Party shall independently obtain and maintain appropriate workers compensation insurance to provide minimum coverage to comply with all applicable laws including, but not limited to, any statutory obligation imposed by workers compensation or occupational disease laws. (c) Other. Prior to granting access to the Shared Premises to others, each Party will require that any authorized individuals having access to the Shared Premises will Exhibit D-1-2 4812-9092-4561.2OHSUSA:751106638.3 either (i) be covered under such Party s insurance applicable to this Agreement or (ii) maintain general liability, automobile liability, and worker s compensation insurance in the types and amounts as indicated above and name both Parties as additional insured as reasonably acceptable to the Parties and in compliance with all applicable laws. (d) Notification of Incidents. Each Party shall promptly notify the other Party as soon as is reasonable possible after the occurrence of any accidents, incidents or events involving the Shared Premises or the Common Facilities which could give rise to a claim under any policy of insurance applicable to this Agreement.

1.	Availability: CED White River Solar, LLC ("Seller") makes electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available under this Tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below. 

2.	Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services by Seller at market-based rates.

3.	Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 

4.	Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.

5.	Ancillary Services. Seller may make available to any purchaser the following ancillary services.
a.	California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO.
b.	Third Party Provider: Seller offers Regulation Service, Energy Imbalance Service, Spinning Reserves, and Supplemental Reserves. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier; and (3) sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers.
6.	Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a), in the Southwest region. Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a), in the Central, Northeast, Northwest, Southeast, and Southwest Power Pool regions.

7.	Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 

8.	Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141, except sections 141.14 and 141.15; and received blanket approval under Part 34.
